The course helps to better understand the relationship and developments between language and society in the Nordic countries as well as the place of different Scandinavian languages in the globalized world. Additionally, it develops the capacity to carry out independent research.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide an overview of the main research areas and methods of sociolinguistics focusing on language variation and change in the Nordic countries. The topics under discussion include sociolinguistic and regional variation of Scandinavian languages, the interrelationship between different Scandinavian languages, and language politics in different Nordic countries.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After participating in the course, the student: - has an understanding of the main research areas and methodological framework of sociolinguistics  - understands the essence and importance of language variation and change in the Nordic countries and the interrelationship between different Scandinavian languages - is able to apply sociolinguistic methods in an independent mini-research paper.
